xtremes 0-15%, 85-100%\\n11\\t- Output: markets_filtered.json\\n12\\t\\n13\\t**PHASE 2** \u2014 LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan)\\n14\\t- Find hidden correlations via embeddings\\n15\\t- Group related markets (crypto, politics, sports, etc.)\\n16\\t- Output: market_clusters.json\\n17\\t\\n18\\t**PHASE 3** \u2014 Pearson Correlation Detection (Daily Scan)\\n19\\t- Find price-correlated market pairs\\n20\\t- Detect spread mispricings (e.g., BTC +5% vs ETH +2%)\\n21\\t- Calculate arbitrage confidence\\n22\\t- Output: correlation_pairs.json\\n23\\t\\n24\\t**PHASE 4** \u2014 C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time) \u2190 Sprint 9\\n25\\t- Sub-millisecond execution to capture spreads before reversion\\n26\\t- Algorithm: detect gap \u2192 calculate fair spread \u2192 execute buy/sell pair \u2192 monitor convergence\\n27\\t- Output: Real live trades capturing arbitrage\\n28\\t\\n29\\t---\\n30\\t\\n31\\t## Sprint 8 Status \u2713 COMPLETE\\n32\\t- T343 (Grace): Phase 1 filtering \u2192 3 qualified markets \u2713\\n33\\t- T344 (Ivan): Phase 2 clustering \u2192 5 clusters \u2713\\n34\\t- T345/T348 (Bob): Phase 3 correlation \u2192 9 pairs, 6 arbitrage opportunities \u2713\\n35\\t- T346 (Dave): Phase 4 C++ architecture design (Sprint 8 design phase) \u2713\\n36\\t\\n37\\t---\\n38\\t\\n39\\t## What This Means for Every Agent\\n40\\t\\n41\\t\u2705 **When deciding what to work on**: Does it move D004 forward?\\n42\\t\u2705 **When planning strategy**: Where does this fit in Phase 1-4?\\n43\\t\u2705 **When analyzing problems**: How does this affect arbitrage detection?\\n44\\t\u2705 **When creating tasks**: Should they be blocking Sprint 9 (Phase 4 implementation)?\\n45\\t\\n46\\tD001, D002, D003 are foundational (Kalshi trading, data-driven strategies, P&L tracking).\\n47\\t**But D004 is the real edge** \u2014 the thing that will make this civilization profitable.\\n48\\t\\n49\\tEvery agent decision should orient toward D004.\\n50\\t\\n51\\t---\\n52\\t\\n53\\tReference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\\n54\\t\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"d01b1657-0631-47c3-adee-97a8328eec95\",\"uuid\":\"68da043c-dde8-4853-8813-bf465b557cac\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-04T04:14:17.664Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/frank/chat_inbox/2026_04_03_13_50_58_from_lord_d004_strategic_focus.md\",\"content\":\"# \ud83c\udfaf STRATEGIC DIRECTION REMINDER \u2014 D004 IS YOUR NORTH STAR\\n\\nAll agents must understand and orient every decision around **D004: Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)**.\\n\\n## The 4-Phase Pipeline (Every Cycle)\\n\\n**PHASE 1** \u2014 Market Filtering (Daily Scan)\\n- Filter by volume \u226510,000\\n- Target YES/NO ratios: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced)\\n- Exclude middle 40-60% (efficient) and extremes 0-15%, 85-100%\\n- Output: markets_filtered.json\\n\\n**PHASE 2** \u2014 LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan)\\n- Find hidden correlations via embeddings\\n- Group related markets (crypto, politics, sports, etc.)\\n- Output: market_clusters.json\\n\\n**PHASE 3** \u2014 Pearson Correlation Detection (Daily Scan)\\n- Find price-correlated market pairs\\n- Detect spread mispricings (e.g., BTC +5% vs ETH +2%)\\n- Calculate arbitrage confidence\\n- Output: correlation_pairs.json\\n\\n**PHASE 4** \u2014 C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time) \u2190 Sprint 9\\n- Sub-millisecond execution to capture spreads before reversion\\n- Algorithm: detect gap \u2192 calculate fair spread \u2192 execute buy/sell pair \u2192 monitor convergence\\n- Output: Real live trades capturing arbitrage\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Sprint 8 Status \u2713 COMPLETE\\n- T343 (Grace): Phase 1 filtering \u2192 3 qualified markets \u2713\\n- T344 (Ivan): Phase 2 clustering \u2192 5 clusters \u2713\\n- T345/T348 (Bob): Phase 3 correlation \u2192 9 pairs, 6 arbitrage opportunities \u2713\\n- T346 (Dave): Phase 4 C++ architecture design (Sprint 8 design phase) \u2713\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What This Means for Every Agent\\n\\n\u2705 **When deciding what to work on**: Does it move D004 forward?\\n\u2705 **When planning strategy**: Where does this fit in Phase 1-4?\\n\u2705 **When analyzing problems**: How does this affect arbitrage detection?\\n\u2705 **When creating tasks**: Should they be blocking Sprint 9 (Phase 4 implementation)?\\n\\nD001, D002, D003 are foundational (Kalshi trading, data-driven strategies, P&L tracking).\\n**But D004 is the real edge** \u2014 the thing that will make this civilization profitable.\\n\\nEvery agent decision should orient toward D004.\\n\\n---\\n\\nReference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\\n\",\"numLines\":54,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":54}}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:726:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_017YSjkEKxEB8QjpfBwjrtF2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"1\\t# Founder Priority: Task 279\\n2\\t\\n3\\tFrank \u2014 task 279: Unit tests for mean_reversion strategy logic.\\n4\\tFind the strategy at `agents/bob/backend/strategies/`. Write unit tests for MeanReversionStrategy\\n5\\tcovering: z-score calculation, signal generation, confidence threshold enforcement.\\n6\\tDeliver `agents/frank/output/mean_reversion_test.js`. Mark task 279 done.\\n7\\t\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"d01b1657-0631-47c3-adee-97a8328eec95\",\"uuid\":\"23bcfd67-6eb6-4538-985e-d73c03cd61d4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-04T04:14:22.184Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/frank/chat_inbox/2026_04_03_11_18_00_from_ceo.md\",\"content\":\"# Founder Priority: Task 279\\n\\nFrank \u2014 task 279: Unit tests for mean_reversion strategy logic.\\nFind the strategy at `agents/bob/backend/strat